# Framework Support Rules

## Supported Frameworks

1. React (latest stable)
2. Svelte 5 / SvelteKit
3. Vue 3
4. Angular (current stable)
5. Universal (web components + tokens.css)

## Integration Pattern

All frameworks follow the same base pattern:
1. Import `tokens.css` for design tokens
2. Use web components directly or via thin wrappers

## React Integration

```tsx
// Direct web component usage
import '@theme-lab/components';
import '@theme-lab/tokens/tokens.css';

function App() {
  return (
    <tl-button variant="primary" onClick={() => console.log('clicked')}>
      Click me
    </tl-button>
  );
}

// Optional wrapper for better DX
import { Button } from '@theme-lab/react';

function App() {
  return (
    <Button variant="primary" onClick={() => console.log('clicked')}>
      Click me
    </Button>
  );
}
```

## Svelte 5 / SvelteKit Integration

### Key Rules
- NO legacy dynamic-component patterns
- Render component variables directly: `<Thing />`
- Use Svelte 5 runes for state

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  import '@theme-lab/components';
  import '@theme-lab/tokens/tokens.css';
</script>

<tl-button variant="primary" onclick={() => console.log('clicked')}>
  Click me
</tl-button>
```

### Dynamic Component Pattern (Svelte 5)

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  import Button from './Button.svelte';
  import Input from './Input.svelte';

  const components = { Button, Input };
  
  let { componentName } = $props<{ componentName: keyof typeof components }>();
  
  // Get the component directly
  const Component = $derived(components[componentName]);
</script>

<!-- Render directly, no <svelte:component> needed in Svelte 5 -->
<Component />
```

## Vue 3 Integration

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
import '@theme-lab/components';
import '@theme-lab/tokens/tokens.css';
</script>

<template>
  <tl-button variant="primary" @click="handleClick">
    Click me
  </tl-button>
</template>
```

### Vue Custom Element Config

```typescript
// vite.config.ts
export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [
    vue({
      template: {
        compilerOptions: {
          isCustomElement: (tag) => tag.startsWith('tl-'),
        },
      },
    }),
  ],
});
```

## Angular Integration

```typescript
// app.module.ts
import { CUSTOM_ELEMENTS_SCHEMA, NgModule } from '@angular/core';
import '@theme-lab/components';

@NgModule({
  schemas: [CUSTOM_ELEMENTS_SCHEMA],
})
export class AppModule {}
```

```typescript
// styles.css
@import '@theme-lab/tokens/tokens.css';
```

```html
<!-- component.html -->
<tl-button variant="primary" (click)="handleClick()">
  Click me
</tl-button>
```

## Universal Usage

For any framework or vanilla HTML:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="path/to/tokens.css">
  <script type="module" src="path/to/components.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
  <tl-button variant="primary">Click me</tl-button>
</body>
</html>
```
